No, just &quot;Do I know you?&quot; Shaking his head Andy had to grin. &quot;I do not believe so, I'm Andy.&quot; Remembering his failure he decided to try with this girl, what the hell he thought. &quot;Do you know a girl named Nefertiti, I was told she might be here, but from the info I just got I might as well give up.&quot; Grinning again, Andy reached into his pocket again, he didn't like the way the hair on the back of his neck kept sticking up. Looking over his shoulder absently he understood why. The police were following him. &quot;Sir could you take your hands out of your pockets?&quot; Looking to the girl, she was no where to be seen. &quot;No, I can't. I think I'll leave em where they are, if you don't have a problem with that.&quot; Obviously they did. Being thrown on the ground, Andy didn't even remember being struck. What the hell. He thought when his knife was lifted from his coat by an invisable hand. &quot;Ok, that is it!&quot; Standing up again he took yet another knife, one he hadn't ever used, only honed. &quot;You can leave me alone, or I can leave you in pieces!&quot; He roared. Surprised again as they dropped his knife and slowly backed away. Andy smiled, even back home the officals would never give him that much respect, they always called his bluff. He put the knife back in his boot and picked the other one up from the side of the street. His smile was gone as he was thrown again up against a wall by no one, there were no police by anymore, there was no one to be seen. Feeling a persistant numbing feeling his his head, Andy just let go and gave up. What the hell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=paradisetheheretic>Paradise the Heretic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://Auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/paradise.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Decay</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/03 9:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/paradise.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i smell bacon</span><hr size=1> Mika apeared from the shadows of the nearby alley.  Growing up on the streets had taught her that the police are, if nothing else, the enemy.  She had also learned that intimidation was sometimes the best weapon.  she hefted her shoulders and tried as hard as she could to be 'intimidating'.  &quot;Now,&quot;  she began, staring Andy coldly in the eyes.  &quot;Who the @#%$ are you and what the @#%$ do you know about Neferiti?&quot;<br>
Mika tweaked her mind and the knife that rested in Andy's boot poped loose and slid through the air, coming to a rest in her hand.  she knew that it's safer to trust no one than to blindly trust a stranger and wind up regretting it.<br>
<br>
&quot;now, explain yourself, before i run you through.&quot; <br>
<br>
her eye twinkled.<br>
