en years to learn such an ability and in his current stage he might appear INSIDE her.  The throbbing increased, always steady, always pulsing.  His strength and resolution where fading quickly and still, he had found no hint of her.  As tears of frustration and pain streamed down his face, he gave up.  He had failed again.  (Your always failing Jerron, thats why they leave you.  Thats why there goooone)  It had taken him twenty minutes to build the courage to try to mentally find her, and he had failed.  The pain in his head increased, even without tapping into his mentalities.  Thud, Thud, Thud.  You....have....failed...Thud, Thud, Thud. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/03 10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I'm lost</span><hr size=1> (OOC-Guys I've gotta be taking a small break from the site... I know that with all the people coming back ya'll should be fine without me anyways. I'm too confused to even try to continue before going back and reading the last one of these. so I'll check back sometime later. Umm my guy is at an inn so don't worry bout him... Someone was interacting with him. umm.. yuou can leave him or act for me or something. but I'll be back later)<br>
